---
import cassetteSvg from "../images/decorative/cassette.svg";
import computerSvg from "../images/decorative/computer.svg";
import lightningSvg from "../images/decorative/lightning.svg";
---

<section id="about" class="cst-bg-grid relative overflow-hidden bg-stone-100">
  <!-- Background Images -->
  <img
    src={cassetteSvg.src}
    alt=""
    class="absolute -left-28 -top-40 z-10 h-[480px] w-[480px]"
  />
  <img
    src={lightningSvg.src}
    alt=""
    class="absolute left-1/2 z-10 h-[540px] w-[540px] -translate-x-1/2 translate-y-1/4 lg:-top-1/4"
  />
  <img
    src={computerSvg.src}
    alt=""
    class="absolute -bottom-48 -right-40 z-10 h-[540px] w-[540px]"
  />

  <!-- Content -->
  <div
    class="container mx-auto flex w-full flex-col gap-8 p-4 md:p-12 lg:flex-row lg:justify-center"
  >
    <div
      class="cst-list-border relative z-20 w-full shrink-0 bg-white lg:basis-1/2"
    >
      <div class="w-full bg-boldPurple p-3">
        <h2 class="font-audiowide text-2xl text-pastelGreen">
          My Strengths üí™
        </h2>
      </div>

      <ul
        class="cst-highlight-strong cst-highlight-strong--purple ml-0 list-outside space-y-2 py-4 pl-7 pr-4"
      >
        <li>
          <strong>Like, 5 Years of React.js Awesomeness.</strong> I've been
          rocking React.js for 5 years straight, making those websites pop like
          totally rad neon colors!
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Core Web Tech Guru.</strong> I've got the 411 on HTML, CSS,
          and JS, and I've been crushing it for, like, 5 years. I'm totally in
          my element with these web goodies!
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Super Flexible, Ready to Rock Any Area.</strong> I'm, like,
          insanely flexible, you know? I'll totally jump into different zones,
          like UI design and backend, to make things happen and ship it, no
          sweat! üòÑüëç
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Always Learning, Always Groovin'.</strong> I'm, like, totally
          committed to learning, improving, and growing, because life's all
          about riding the wave and staying groovy, ya know?
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div
      class="cst-list-border relative z-20 w-full shrink-0 bg-white lg:basis-1/2"
    >
      <div class="w-full bg-pastelGreen p-3">
        <h2 class="font-audiowide text-2xl text-boldPurple">
          My Aspirations ü§©
        </h2>
      </div>

      <ul
        class="cst-highlight-strong cst-highlight-strong--yellow ml-0 list-outside space-y-2 py-4 pl-7 pr-4"
      >
        <li>
          <strong>Laying the Full-Stack Foundation.</strong> I'm all about
          building the rad foundations for full-stack action by diving into
          backend tech and making deployments happen.
        </li>

        <li>
          <strong>3D Rendering Magic with three.js.</strong> I'm on a journey to
          learn and rock those 3D rendering tools like{" "}<a
            href="https://threejs.org/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow"
            class="underline">three.js</a
          >. Gonna make those visuals pop!
        </li>

        <li>
          <strong>Kicking Imposter Syndrome to the Curb.</strong> OMG, imposter
          syndrome? I'm showing it the exit, 'cause I'm a total boss and I know
          it! üòéü§ò
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <style>
    .cst-bg-grid {
      background-image: linear-gradient(rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1) 1px, transparent 1px),
        linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1) 1px, transparent 1px);
      background-size: 40px 40px; /* Adjust the grid size as needed */
    }

    .cst-list-border {
      border: 8px solid;
      border-color: darkorchid orchid;
      outline: 8px ridge lightpink;
    }

    .cst-highlight-strong strong {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 1px 6px 7px;
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-decoration-color: rgb(var(--clr-pastel-green));
      text-decoration-thickness: 4px;
      text-underline-offset: 4px;
    }

    .cst-highlight-strong--purple strong {
      background-color: rgb(var(--clr-bold-purple));
      color: rgb(var(--clr-summer-yellow));
    }

    .cst-highlight-strong--yellow strong {
      background-color: rgb(var(--clr-summer-yellow));
      color: rgb(var(--clr-bold-purple));
    }
  </style>
</section>
